column1: Which film will win the 2020 Golden Globe for Best Motion Picture - Musical or Comedy?
column5: ['Dolemite Is My Name', 'Jojo Rabbit', 'Knives Out', 'Once Upon a Time...in Hollywood', 'Rocketman', 'A tie or other outcome']

column6: I have Once Upon a Time as the razor-thin favorite vs. everything else. If Once Upon a Time did not exist, I'd say Knives Out.
Admittedly, I've only seen one of these films (Once upon a time in Hollywood); my estimates are based upon comments I've heard from friends and some press buzz.
Going up on Dolemite - First R movie - snuck in with the rest of the Key Club while we were touring D.C. Made an impression.
Eddie Murphy is due. His performance, as always, is superb.
Too early to call as not heard of half of them

Tarantino is the standout based on critical reviews. Knives Out seems lightweight in comparison but has a slight dark-horse chance based on its casting of old and new favorites and Daniel Craig in an unusual comic role.
